.SH "NAME"
POE::Resource::FileHandles \- internal filehandle manager for POE::Kernel
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
There is no public \s-1API.\s0
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
POE::Resource::FileHandles is a mix-in class for POE::Kernel.  It
provides the low-level features to manage filehandles.  It is used
internally by POE::Kernel, so it has no public interface.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
See \*(L"I/O Watchers (Selects)\*(R" in POE::Kernel for the public file watcher
\&\s-1API.\s0
.PP
See \*(L"Resources\*(R" in POE::Kernel for public information about \s-1POE\s0
resources.
.PP
See POE::Resource for general discussion about resources and the
classes that manage them.
.SH "BUGS"
.IX Header "BUGS"
\&\s-1POE\s0 watches I/O based on filehandles rather than file descriptors,
which means there can be clashes between its \s-1API\s0 and an underlying
descriptor-based event loop.  This is usually not a problem, but it
may require a work-around in certain edge cases.
